article.description: Ed Drew had career-highs of 22 points and 12 rebounds, and DeSean Murray added 18 points to help Presbyterian beat Toccoa Falls 116-75 on Wednesday night for the Blue Hose's second 100-point game
article.headline: Ed Drew, Presbyterian beat Toccoa Falls 116-75
article.linkText: Ed Drew, Presbyterian beat Toccoa Falls 116-75
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Ed Drew had career-highs of 22 points and 12 rebounds, and DeSean Murray added 18 points to help Presbyterian beat Toccoa Falls 116-75 on Wednesday night for the Blue Hose's second 100-point game in program history. It was the most points for Presbyterian in its Division I era, topping 111 scored against Carver Bible College in 2008. Drew was 10 of 13 from the field, and Murray made 6 of 8 shots and had four of Presbyterian's 14 steals. John Majors II added 17 points and seven rebounds for Presbyterian (2-1), which outrebounded Toccoa Falls 56-42. The Blue Hose did struggle from the 3-point line, making just 3 of 23 shots. Connor Iverson and Josh Folwell scored 14 points apiece for Toccoa Falls, a NCCAA Division II member. The Eagles turned it over 23 times and were 27-of-74 shooting (37 percent), including 1 of 16 from 3-point range.
